Five-Year Accident History

Within the past five years, the Lake Hartwell Filter Plant has not had an accidental release of chlorine. The plant has maintained an excellent safety record and we know of no accidental chlorine release throughout its more than 30 year operating history .  

Emergency Response

In the event that a chlorine release does occur, the Lake Hartwell Filter Plant has an emergency response program that coordinates emergency response with the Anderson County LEPC. If such a release did occur, plant personnel would contact the Anderson County LEPC who would dispatch a trained HAZMAT team to the site to handle the chlorine release. 

